# Auth UI and Session UX Rule

## Keycloak Identity

The app uses Keycloak as the identity provider.

Never ask normal users to manually type UUID, user_id, keycloak_id, or internal identifiers.

User identity must come from the authenticated session/JWT.

## Login UX

Login page must be a real branded auth page, not a giant hero or redirect placeholder.

Required:
- brand
- short value proposition
- one clear primary login CTA
- secondary return-home link
- loading state
- error state
- accessible contrast

Forbidden:
- invisible button text
- disabled-looking CTA when clickable
- manual UUID input
- custom password auth unless explicitly requested
- local fake auth in production UI

## Layout

Learner routes must use shared AppShell.

Admin routes must use AdminShell.

Header/nav must not disappear between pages.

## Button Accessibility

All button variants must pass contrast.

Primary buttons must have clearly visible text in normal, hover, focus, active, and disabled states.

Focus rings must not obscure labels.

## Auth-aware UI

Unauthenticated:
- show login CTA
- explain benefits of login
- allow limited public browsing if supported

Authenticated:
- show display name/avatar
- show personalized Today Plan
- use session user ID internally

Never show internal technical identifiers in normal learner UI.

## Implementation Detail Hiding

Never expose infrastructure names to end users.

Forbidden user-facing words:
- Keycloak
- OIDC
- OAuth
- realm
- client_id
- access_token
- refresh_token
- UUID
- JWT

Use product language instead:
- Đăng nhập
- Tạo tài khoản
- Đồng bộ tiến độ
- Tiếp tục học
- Phiên đăng nhập đã hết hạn